# Tailwind Styling Rules - ATM Design System

## Core Principle: Use Tailwind v4 Theme Variable Namespaces

Tailwind v4 **automatically generates utility classes** from theme variables defined in specific namespaces. Use these auto-generated utilities instead of arbitrary value syntax.

Reference: [Tailwind v4 Theme Variable Namespaces](https://tailwindcss.com/docs/theme#theme-variable-namespaces)

---

## Key Namespaces That Auto-Generate Utilities

| Namespace | Auto-generates | Example Token → Utility |
|-----------|----------------|------------------------|
| `--spacing-*` | Spacing & sizing | `--spacing-button-gap` → `gap-button-gap` |
| `--radius-*` | Border radius | `--radius-button` → `rounded-button` |
| `--color-*` | Colors | `--color-brand-accent` → `bg-brand-accent` |
| `--text-*` | Font sizes | `--text-button-lg` → `text-button-lg` |
| `--shadow-*` | Box shadows | `--shadow-card` → `shadow-card` |
| `--font-*` | Font families | `--font-ubuntu` → `font-ubuntu` |

---

## The Rules

### 0. No Magic Values in Components

- **Never** use arbitrary values like `w-[48px]`, `rounded-[12px]`, `shadow-[...]` in `*.tsx`
- **Never** use raw palette primitives like `text-blue-500`, `bg-slate-50`, `border-gray-200`
- **Always** use semantic/component tokens (Tier 2 / Tier 3) via:
  - Auto-generated utilities (preferred): `w-news-card-image-width`, `rounded-news-card`, `shadow-news-card`
  - Variable syntax only when the token **cannot** generate utilities (see “When CSS Variable Syntax IS Needed”)

### 1. Define Tokens in Correct Namespaces

```css
@theme {
  /* ✅ CORRECT - Uses --spacing-* namespace */
  --spacing-button-height-lg: 44px;    /* → h-button-height-lg */
  --spacing-button-height-sm: 36px;    /* → h-button-height-sm */
  --spacing-button-padding-x-lg: 24px; /* → px-button-padding-x-lg */
  --spacing-button-gap: 8px;           /* → gap-button-gap */
  --spacing-button-icon-lg: 24px;      /* → size-button-icon-lg */
  
  /* ✅ CORRECT - Uses --radius-* namespace */
  --radius-button: 4px;                /* → rounded-button */
  
  /* ❌ WRONG - --size-* is NOT a valid namespace */
  --size-button-height-lg: 44px;       /* Won't generate utilities! */
}
```

### 2. Use Auto-Generated Utility Classes

```jsx
// ✅ CORRECT - Use auto-generated utilities
<button className="h-button-height-lg px-button-padding-x-lg rounded-button gap-button-gap">
  Click me
</button>

// ✅ CORRECT - Component tokens (News Card example)
<article className="rounded-news-card shadow-news-card min-h-news-card-min-height-default">
  ...
</article>

// ❌ WRONG - Don't use CSS variable syntax when namespace utilities exist
<button className="h-(--spacing-button-height-lg) px-(--spacing-button-padding-x-lg)">
  Click me
</button>

// ❌ WRONG - Never use var() arbitrary syntax
<button className="h-[var(--spacing-button-height-lg)]">
  Click me
</button>
```

### 3. Use Semantic Classes for Colors

```jsx
// ✅ CORRECT - Semantic color classes from tailwind.config.js
<button className="bg-brand-accent text-content-inverse hover:bg-accent-surface">
  Click me
</button>

// ❌ WRONG - CSS variable syntax for colors
<button className="bg-[var(--color-brand-accent)]">
  Click me
</button>
```

